         <abstract>
            <p>Since diesel engine oils are part of the low-emission equation, there has been stepped increases in the quality of crankcase oils with the stepped reduction in diesel exhaust emissions. The new API CG-4 oil category, was developed to address the Engine Manufacturers Association's (EMA's) needs for 1994 emission-controlled diesel engines. It also improves the quality of crankcase oils by using modern four-cycle diesel engine tests which: • operate on low-sulfur diesel fuel, as used by all on-highway trucks in the U. S., • have statistically defined test limits, • are incorporated into the Chemical Manufacturers Association's (CMA's) rigorous code for qualification testing.</p>
         </abstract>
